==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prosenchyma
<hw>Pros*en"chy*ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ near + <ets>-enchyma</ets>, as in <ets>parenchyma</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A general term applied to the tissues formed of
elongated cells, especially those with pointed or oblique extremities,
as the principal cells of ordinary wood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

